   C&R Banner
   Functions and responsibilities of the Coordination and Requirements
   Section include:
     * Coordinating mapping activities with Federal, State, and local
       governments and the private sector in the 15 Mid-Continent Mapping
       Center States.
     * Determining and analyzing users requirements for mapping,
       derivative map products, and spatial digital data.
     * Establishing cooperative agreements for map and digital data
       production with interested agencies and coordinating the
       development of innovative partnerships between these agencies.
     * Conducting research and resolving difficult problems involving
       cartographic and geographic data.
     * Assisting and informing Federal, State, and local agencies and the
       public through presentations and demonstrations on the National
       Mapping Programs and the activities of the National Mapping
       Division.
     * Serving as the coordinator when approached by governmental agencies
       and the private sector who possess non-National Mapping Division
       digital data.
     * Explaining the role of the USGS in the National Spatial Data
       Infrastructure (NSDI) and related Federal Geographic Data Committee
       (FGDC) activities.

